Oman Central Bank Allows Lenders to Open Islamic Branches

-- B y   D a n a   E l   B a l t a j i
-- 
2011-05-30T05:31:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/oman-central-bank-allows-lenders-to-open-islamic-branches.html
Oman’s  Central Bank  is allowing non-
Islamic lenders to open Shariah-compliant branches to offer
products that comply with the religion’s ban on interest, the
regulator said in a statement published by state-run  Oman News
Agency  dated yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dana El Baltaji in Dubai at 
 delbaltaji@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  